00:09:23,564 --> 00:09:25,430
murdered
Officer John Decker

263
00:09:25,432 --> 00:09:27,632
and paid Joe Fields to go
   to prison for that crime.

264
00:09:27,634 --> 00:09:29,401
Oh, and when Fields
wanted out of their deal,

265
00:09:29,403 --> 00:09:30,435
Perry also killed him.

266
00:09:30,437 --> 00:09:31,703
Your Honor,
     with all due respect,

267
00:09:31,705 --> 00:09:32,704
granting a dismissal

268
00:09:32,706 --> 00:09:33,939
would be ludicrous.

269
00:09:33,941 --> 00:09:35,006
Boris Sokolov's death,

270
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:38,076
while undoubtedly tragic,

271
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:40,712
changes nothing.

272
00:09:40,714 --> 00:09:42,948
Well, the defense agrees.

273
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,349
What?

274
00:09:44,351 --> 00:09:46,851
His death doesn't
change a single thing.

275
00:09:46,853 --> 00:09:49,521
With or without
Mr. Sokolov's testimony,

276
00:09:49,523 --> 00:09:51,056
my client should never
have been charged

277
00:09:51,058 --> 00:09:52,123
with these crimes.

278
00:09:53,427 --> 00:09:54,426
Well...

279
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:56,895
seeing as both parties agree,

280
00:09:56,897 --> 00:09:58,597
the trial will proceed
          immediately.

281
00:09:58,599 --> 00:09:59,598
Actually, Your Honor,

282
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,999
the State would like to, uh,

283
00:10:01,001 --> 00:10:02,100
request a continuance.

284
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,402
In light of the death
of our key witness,

285
00:10:04,404 --> 00:10:07,105
our office needs time
       to, uh, reexamine

286
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:08,607
its strategy.

287
00:10:08,609 --> 00:10:09,741
But I'm confused,
                     Your Honor.

288
00:10:09,743 --> 00:10:11,509
Didn't we just hear
the prosecution say

289
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:13,712
their case was
"unshakable"?

290
00:10:13,714 --> 00:10:15,447
We did.

291
00:10:15,449 --> 00:10:16,548
Request denied.

292
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:20,018
Session will resume after lunch.

293
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:26,791
What the hell are you doing,
            Mother?

294
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:28,026
Oh, calm down, Lucifer.

295
00:10:28,028 --> 00:10:29,594
This isn't pleasant
for me, either.

296
00:10:29,596 --> 00:10:31,696
Oh, yes, I can see
   you're suffering terribly.

297
00:10:31,698 --> 00:10:33,898
I was good up there,
wasn't I?

298
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:36,434
Not sure why humans spend
so much time in law school.

299
00:10:36,436 --> 00:10:37,469
Two nights seemed plenty.

300
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:38,837
Mum.

301
00:10:38,839 --> 00:10:41,640
I had to find a way
to open your eyes.

302
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:43,642
You need to see that
this Chloe you so adore

303
00:10:43,644 --> 00:10:44,643
isn't worthy of you.

304
00:10:44,645 --> 00:10:45,744
(scoffs)

305
00:10:45,746 --> 00:10:47,045
I admit I enjoy working
            with her, but adore,

306
00:10:47,047 --> 00:10:48,446
that's a bit much.

307
00:10:48,448 --> 00:10:50,649
Oh, please. You've sacrificed
          more for her

308
00:10:50,651 --> 00:10:52,450
than you ever have
        for anyone else.

309
00:10:52,452 --> 00:10:55,153
Have you forgotten?
        You killed your brother,

310
00:10:55,155 --> 00:10:56,655
my son, to protect her.

311
00:10:56,657 --> 00:11:00,058
Do you think there's anything
           even remotely similar

312
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:01,059
that she would do for you?

313
00:11:01,061 --> 00:11:03,094
I suppose...

314
00:11:03,096 --> 00:11:04,663
I don't know.

315
00:11:04,665 --> 00:11:06,698
Well, if all goes according
      to plan in that courtroom,

316
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:07,966
you will know.

317
00:11:07,968 --> 00:11:09,634
Know that she doesn't
                    deserve you,

318
00:11:09,636 --> 00:11:10,935
because she doesn't
                  care about you

319
00:11:10,937 --> 00:11:12,671
like you care about her.

320
00:11:12,673 --> 00:11:14,773
You need to see that you're
       not meant to be together.

321
00:11:14,775 --> 00:11:16,808
You belong with your family.

322
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:18,543
Which is why
       I have to do this.

323
00:11:18,545 --> 00:11:20,211
Do what, Mum?

324
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:24,916
What sort of evil plan
      are you concocting?

325
00:11:24,918 --> 00:11:27,419
And please don't tell me
   it began by killing Boris.

326
00:11:27,421 --> 00:11:29,454
Oh, actually, that was
     just a happy twist of fate.

327
00:11:29,456 --> 00:11:30,689
I was gonna
                  blow Chloe up,

328
00:11:30,691 --> 00:11:31,923
but Amenadiel
            talked me out of it.

329
00:11:31,925 --> 00:11:33,958
You what?!

330
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:37,095
Mother, I swear,
 if you hurt her, I will rip--

331
00:11:37,097 --> 00:11:39,130
Well, looks like
         your brother was right.

332
00:11:41,134 --> 00:11:43,702
Just promise me that
      you won't touch her.

333
00:11:45,806 --> 00:11:48,139
I'm not going to hurt anyone.

334
00:11:53,947 --> 00:11:55,680
Lucifer, you promise me,

335
00:11:55,682 --> 00:11:58,717
whatever that was, that
    it doesn't affect the trial.

336
00:11:58,719 --> 00:12:00,785
First of all, Detective,
there is no "that."

337
00:12:00,787 --> 00:12:05,690
And secondly, rest assured,
everything will be okay.

338
00:12:05,692 --> 00:12:07,125
I've got this.

339
00:12:15,168 --> 00:12:17,068
You looking for Boris'
forensics report?

340
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,069
(sighs)

341
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:19,070
Uh-huh.

342
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:20,472
Hasn't come in yet.

343
00:12:20,474 --> 00:12:22,107
Ella should have it
any minute now.

344
00:12:22,109 --> 00:12:25,210
I know this isn't my case,
      but I'm freaking out, Dan.

345
00:12:25,212 --> 00:12:26,878
I can't let Perry get
           away with everything.

346
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,146
You won't.

347
00:12:28,148 --> 00:12:30,148
You didn't see Charlotte
        Richards in court today.

348
00:12:30,150 --> 00:12:31,516
(high-pitched): Char--?
      (clears his throat)

349
00:12:31,518 --> 00:12:32,550
I'm sorry. Uh,

350
00:12:32,552 --> 00:12:34,686
Charlotte Richards
is, uh, defending Perry?

351
00:12:34,688 --> 00:12:35,754
Yeah.

352
00:12:35,756 --> 00:12:37,756
Really?
She's that good?

353
00:12:37,758 --> 00:12:39,691
Yes, she's
                       the best.

354
00:12:39,693 --> 00:12:41,693
Which is why it would
        be helpful if we could--

355
00:12:41,695 --> 00:12:43,695
Well, if you could tie
         Perry to Boris' murder.

356
00:12:43,697 --> 00:12:46,131
Okay, well, motive
and M.O. line up.

357
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:47,699
Boris' tongue was cut out.

358
00:12:47,701 --> 00:12:51,002
So the killer was sending
a really clear message--

359
00:12:51,004 --> 00:12:52,771
loose lips get
their head clipped.

360
00:12:52,773 --> 00:12:55,774
Perry did this so Boris
    couldn't testify, I know it.

361
00:12:55,776 --> 00:12:58,143
But hasn't he been behind bars
since you arrested him?

362
00:12:58,145 --> 00:12:59,577
Yeah, but he could have
   orchestrated it in prison.

363
00:12:59,579 --> 00:13:00,645
It's also his M.O.

364
00:13:00,647 --> 00:13:02,647
Exactly, and if Perry
            is good at anything,

365
00:13:02,649 --> 00:13:04,182
it's making other people
             pay for his crimes.

366
00:13:04,184 --> 00:13:06,151
Okay, well, whoever
Perry hired to do this

367
00:13:06,153 --> 00:13:07,285
was one sharp dude.

368
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:10,054
The cut on Boris' neck
is extremely precise.

369
00:13:10,056 --> 00:13:13,057
I'm thinking industrial-size
professional slicer.

370
00:13:13,059 --> 00:13:16,928
Listen, I'm gonna do
 everything I can to find him.

371
00:13:16,930 --> 00:13:18,930
Even if I have to interview
           the owner

372
00:13:18,932 --> 00:13:20,298
of every single
      meat slicer in L.A.

373
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:22,167
ELLA:
You won't have to.

374
00:13:22,169 --> 00:13:25,136
There was also
non-human DNA on Boris.

375
00:13:25,138 --> 00:13:27,071
Swine, to be exact.

376
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:29,674
A unique cross-bred
for its delicious meat.

377
00:13:29,676 --> 00:13:32,076
And there's only
one place that sells it.

378
00:13:35,715 --> 00:13:36,948
Ah!

379
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:38,683
Hi.

380
00:13:38,685 --> 00:13:40,218
That's so sweet of you, but you
  don't have to stick around.

381
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:41,786
Trials can be so boring.
Well,

382
00:13:41,788 --> 00:13:42,887
not this one.

383
00:13:42,889 --> 00:13:43,822
What do you mean?

384
00:13:43,824 --> 00:13:44,856
Mr. Morningstar,

385
00:13:44,858 --> 00:13:46,658
we're ready for you.

386
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,693
Wonderful.
         Lovely. Right.

387
00:13:48,695 --> 00:13:52,063
Off I go to shield you from
that Quid Pro Ho, Detective.

388
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:54,332
Lucifer, what are you doing?

389
00:13:54,334 --> 00:13:56,701
Well, I figured
there's no reason for us

390
00:13:56,703 --> 00:13:59,904
to lose our heads just
because Boris lost his.

391
00:14:01,908 --> 00:14:04,642
I swear to tell the truth,
                the whole truth,

392
00:14:04,644 --> 00:14:07,245
and nothing but the truth,

393
00:14:07,247 --> 00:14:08,413
so help me Dad.

394
00:14:16,122 --> 00:14:17,255
Mr. Morningstar,

395
00:14:17,257 --> 00:14:20,191
you were there
    when Boris was arrested.

396
00:14:20,193 --> 00:14:22,260
Right? Working with
Detective Espinoza.

397
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:24,229
That is correct.

398
00:14:24,231 --> 00:14:26,064
Except I call him
       Detective Douche.

399
00:14:26,066 --> 00:14:27,332
(laughter)

400
00:14:27,334 --> 00:14:28,933
But that's another story.

401
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:32,003
So would you
please describe to us

402
00:14:32,005 --> 00:14:33,137
what happened?

403
00:14:33,139 --> 00:14:34,372
Yes, I'd love to, actually.

404
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:35,506
May-may I have the floor?

405
00:14:35,508 --> 00:14:36,541
By all means.

406
00:14:36,543 --> 00:14:38,276
LUCIFER:
                      Thank you.

407
00:14:38,278 --> 00:14:40,278
I'm going to need...

408
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:42,247
Hello.

409
00:14:42,249 --> 00:14:43,481
May I borrow your scarf?

410
00:14:43,483 --> 00:14:46,017
Your Honor,
is this necessary?

411
00:14:46,019 --> 00:14:48,253
Well, you want
   the full story, don't you?

412
00:14:48,255 --> 00:14:50,154
I mean, the Devil's
        in the details.

413
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:52,190
Thank you ever so much.

414
00:14:53,293 --> 00:14:56,294
Right. Myself
     and Detective Douche--

415
00:14:56,296 --> 00:14:57,629
sorry, Detective Espinoza--

416
00:14:57,631 --> 00:14:59,397
were asked by the LAPD

417
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,165
to perform a sting operation.

418
00:15:01,167 --> 00:15:02,267
Not the singer.

419
00:15:02,269 --> 00:15:05,136
(laughter)
   So we had to go undercover

420
00:15:05,138 --> 00:15:06,437
at Boris' bathhouse.

421
00:15:06,439 --> 00:15:07,572
Guns of steel...

422
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:09,574
Got up there...
   (imitated slashing sound)

423
00:15:09,576 --> 00:15:11,276
Walked over like
             he's constantly got

424
00:15:11,278 --> 00:15:12,577
a gun between his legs...

425
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:15,580
Boris looked me in the eye,
          and he said,

426
00:15:15,582 --> 00:15:17,615
(Russian accent): "People call
    me human lie detector."

427
00:15:17,617 --> 00:15:19,050
He was going to kill...

428
00:15:19,052 --> 00:15:21,419
Shook my hand like
 some kind of Roman warrior...

429
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:24,455
...and it was sealed, and I
 handed over the investigation

430
00:15:24,457 --> 00:15:26,991
to Detective Decker.

431
00:15:26,993 --> 00:15:28,393
Thank you.
      (laughter, applause)

432
00:15:28,395 --> 00:15:29,661
¶ Stop draggin' me down ¶

433
00:15:29,663 --> 00:15:31,029
¶ ¶

434
00:15:31,031 --> 00:15:34,399
¶ Stop dragging me down, yeah. ¶

435
00:15:36,436 --> 00:15:37,936
DAN:
       I got a question.

436
00:15:37,938 --> 00:15:40,038
Do you ever get the feeling
          like you've been used?

437
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:42,707
You mean, by--
       oh, I don't know--

438
00:15:42,709 --> 00:15:46,544
the woman who's defending the
 killer of your ex-wife's dad?

439
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:47,645
What?

440
00:15:47,647 --> 00:15:49,614
Charlotte Richards is
       the gorgeous lady

441
00:15:49,616 --> 00:15:50,682
you slept with, right?

442
00:15:50,684 --> 00:15:52,617
How the hell did
                  you know that?

443
00:15:52,619 --> 00:15:55,286
Well, I saw a long,
honey-blonde hair

444
00:15:55,288 --> 00:15:56,554
on your coat the other day.

445
00:15:56,556 --> 00:15:58,957
It was curlier than Chloe's.
And then,

446
00:15:58,959 --> 00:16:00,625
I spotted a smudge of lipstick

447
00:16:00,627 --> 00:16:02,193
on your cuff--
burgundy shade.

448
00:16:02,195 --> 00:16:05,697
Bold, but not too sexy.
         Lawyer color.

449
00:16:05,699 --> 00:16:06,965
Really?

450
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:10,068
No. I just saw
your butt pucker

451
00:16:10,070 --> 00:16:12,370
when Chloe mentioned her name
in the lab this morning.

452
00:16:12,372 --> 00:16:14,105
God.

453
00:16:14,107 --> 00:16:16,074
Why are you so worried?

454
00:16:16,076 --> 00:16:17,709
I mean, you didn't tell her
anything about the case

455
00:16:17,711 --> 00:16:19,610
that she could
use in court, right?

456
00:16:19,612 --> 00:16:22,647
I don't think so, but...
There you go.

457
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:24,082
Mezcal cocktails, man.

458
00:16:24,084 --> 00:16:26,217
Oof. Those sneak up on you.

459
00:16:26,219 --> 00:16:28,252
She did keep wanting
         to talk about our exes,

460
00:16:28,254 --> 00:16:30,421
and all I thought was, you know
 what, she's so easy to talk to.

461
00:16:30,423 --> 00:16:31,522
She's so sympathetic.

462
00:16:31,524 --> 00:16:33,057
God, I'm such an idiot.

463
00:16:33,059 --> 00:16:35,126
Hey...
     No, her taking Perry's case

464
00:16:35,128 --> 00:16:36,527
right after we...

465
00:16:36,529 --> 00:16:38,129
It can't be a coincidence.

466
00:16:38,131 --> 00:16:40,264
Why not?

467
00:16:40,266 --> 00:16:42,500
Maybe she really
just likes you.
                           Yeah.

468
00:16:42,502 --> 00:16:44,535
44.
Hi. We'll take

469
00:16:44,537 --> 00:16:46,070
the headless body of a dude
named Boris, please.

470
00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:51,242
I was going
to call you guys.

471
00:16:51,244 --> 00:16:53,077
I was just... scared.

472
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:56,014
A few days ago,
    this guy approached me.

473
00:16:56,016 --> 00:16:57,281
Big creepy dude.

474
00:16:57,283 --> 00:16:59,350
He demanded the keys to use
the equipment after hours.

475
00:16:59,352 --> 00:17:01,552
No questions asked,
        unless I wanted

476
00:17:01,554 --> 00:17:03,021
to end up in the sausage myself.

477
00:17:03,023 --> 00:17:05,023
Do you know his name?
No.

478
00:17:05,025 --> 00:17:07,091
Asian, big.

479
00:17:07,093 --> 00:17:08,493
Very scary.

480
00:17:10,163 --> 00:17:13,765
But the scar on his neck
     it's very distinctive.

481
00:17:15,502 --> 00:17:16,501
Thank you, Mr. Morningstar.

482
00:17:16,503 --> 00:17:18,703
What a, uh, vivid picture.

483
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,572
It's almost as if Boris
himself just testified.

484
00:17:21,574 --> 00:17:23,808
(quietly): Except
a more handsome version.

485
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:25,810
Oh, stop it, Judy.

486
00:17:25,812 --> 00:17:27,045
(chuckles)

487
00:17:27,047 --> 00:17:28,446
(clears throat)
           Thank you.

488
00:17:28,448 --> 00:17:29,647
Right actually,
                        to that,

489
00:17:29,649 --> 00:17:31,149
I would like to add one
         more thing, if I may...

490
00:17:31,151 --> 00:17:33,718
I think we've had
             enough, Your Honor.

491
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,452
Shh!

492
00:17:34,454 --> 00:17:35,586
Please...

493
00:17:35,588 --> 00:17:37,688
continue Luc--

494
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:40,258
Mr. Morningstar.

495
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:42,660
Thank you, my darling.

496
00:17:42,662 --> 00:17:46,130
Yes, I'd just like to say,
                 for the record,

497
00:17:46,132 --> 00:17:49,734
the LAPD, and Detective Decker,
         in particular,

498
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:52,470
acted impeccably
                   on this case.

499
00:17:52,472 --> 00:17:55,640
This whole courtroom,
      nay, the entire city

500
00:17:55,642 --> 00:17:58,342
can rest assured that
       someone as honest,

501
00:17:58,344 --> 00:18:01,746
trustworthy, and reliable
      as Detective Decker

502
00:18:01,748 --> 00:18:04,148
is out there
                protecting them.

503
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:08,619
She is... truly good.

504
00:18:08,621 --> 00:18:10,088
And I don't mean in bed.

505
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:11,589
I wouldn't know.

506
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:13,157
That's how good she is.

507
00:18:14,627 --> 00:18:16,294
Thank you.

508
00:18:16,296 --> 00:18:17,295
Miss Richards?

509
00:18:17,297 --> 00:18:19,797
Your witness.

510
00:18:21,701 --> 00:18:24,802
I have no questions
         at this time.

511
00:18:26,706 --> 00:18:28,706
(thunder crashes)

512
00:18:37,817 --> 00:18:38,883
Hey!

513
00:18:38,885 --> 00:18:40,118
That's Chloe's car.

514
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,185
What are you looking for?

515
00:18:41,187 --> 00:18:42,253
Hey.

516
00:18:43,323 --> 00:18:44,889
I was, um...

517
00:18:44,891 --> 00:18:45,890
You.

518
00:18:45,892 --> 00:18:47,792
I was looking for you.

519
00:18:47,794 --> 00:18:49,393
Really?

520
00:18:49,395 --> 00:18:50,795
Yeah, I've missed you.

521
00:18:52,532 --> 00:18:55,333
It's true, I still
